<subSubSection id="F3B5DAC7CCFE0A06837E28E69A270337" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="C1896FA63B5A7DD2B6ABBED9D355668A" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="62AD95D604D70C00D4431D658752D106" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Growth form regular, massive, rarely exceeding 10 cm in diameter. Colour black or dark grey in vivo. Consistency strong, relatively elastic. Surface finely conulose (1-2 mm in height and 2-3 mm apart). Oscules (up to 1 cm in diameter) irregularly scattered. Skeleton network reticulation of ascending primary fibres (90-180 
<normalizedToken id="E5553AEE07FA5172FB36D9267D82165A" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter) with a fibrous narrow core free of inclusions or bearing only rare spicules. Secondary fibres (50-100 
<normalizedToken id="40A22BEA10D3D3D3EFC3E33DCB6EEC35" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter) uncored and laminated. Filaments (0.7-2.0 
<normalizedToken id="3F9C501D8ACD4F456D1C9335F20FC125" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter) very abundant giving a strong consistency.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="59FCAB2A71D7085B7D8529D17826B0E1" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="99B652B52914EE7AA347DEBD38ADA912" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B2AF59803B9B08CB8D62BBBC5942185" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Cave, rocky, detritic and muddy bottom, coralligenous community, lagoon, 
<taxonomicName id="5A1450A06C7C8C36AD11283E93C88BDF" class="Liliopsida" family="Posidoniaceae" genus="Posidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Posidonia oceanica" order="Alismatales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oceanica">Posidonia oceanica</taxonomicName>
meadow, epibiotic on 
<taxonomicName id="B8B8EBBEEEA612819EB916D25959A9DB" class="Bivalvia" family="Pinnidae" genus="Pinna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pinna nobilis" order="Ostreida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nobilis">Pinna nobilis</taxonomicName>
. Bathymetric range 1-60 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91A3984BDA114FE580F6F5B415D3623F" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="mediterranean caves">
<paragraph id="9C2C532B2117415F250699B51F05F159" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Mediterranean caves.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="08A327BAD57B03A05E2E907937478218" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
